tion 7: Worst Fit with Sinusoidal Oscillation\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    available = np.where(bins >= item, bins - item, -np.inf)\n    return np.sin(np.pi * available / item) + np.exp(-available)\n```\n\n### Implementation 8: Max Fit with Quadratic Penalty\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    available = np.where(bins >= item, bins - item, 0)\n    return np.exp(-available**2) + np.sin(np.pi * available / item)\n```\n\n### Implementation 9: Min Fit with Inverse Tangent\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    available = np.where(bins >= item, bins - item, np.inf)\n    return np.arctan(available) + np.exp(-available)\n```\n\n### Implementation 10: Greedy Fit with Logarithmic Scaling\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    available = np.where(bins >= item, bins - item, 0)\n    return np.log(available + 1) + np.exp(-available)\n'][Process 0] before evaluate_graph[Process 0] func :
